-- Row 45: LDP27
INSERT INTO projects (
    name, description, location, size_sqm, end_date,
    status, project_type, sector,
    user_id,
    external_code, authors, organization, uia_region, selected,
    created_at
) VALUES (
    'Tea Leaf Market of Zhuguanlong',
    'Zhuguanlong Township of Shouning County, Ningde City of Fujian Province, where the Tea Leaf Market is located, is a township fertile in tea leaf yet to be lifted out of poverty at the time of the project’s planning phase. Zhuguanlong Tea Leaf Market featured a multi-functional tea leaf market, aiming for a boost in tea leaf economy and better public spaces for local people..

A large-span space was proposed for various functions at different times of the year based on earlier bamboo construction experience, fundamental functions of the market and other demands by the public. Apart from seasonal tea leaf trading, the market can be used for farm product trading, villagers’ short stay and children’s sports activities. On special occasions such as weddings and funerals, people can also gather under the market’s roof for a feast. 

The project‘s structural form inspired by a sort of traditional woven arch structure built with local raw bamboo. Locally obtained natural materials and recycled building materials such as soil, wood and stone were all used for construction, motivating local craftsmen to wisely “turn wastes into treasures” with refined local building technologies, presenting a well-utilized public building to the villagers. Zhuguanlong Township of Shouning County, Ningde City of Fujian Province, is a township fertile of tea leaf yet to be lifted out of poverty at the time of the project’s planning phase. A multi-purpose large-span space was proposed as a tea market in the town. Apart from seasonal tea leaf trading, the market can be used for farm product trading, villagers’ short stay and children’s sports activities. On special occasions such as weddings, funerals and the local beggar festival, people can also gather under the market’s roof for a feast. 

The design team thoroughly studied building technologies of “rainbow bridge”, a sort of traditional wooden arch bridge achieved with ancient people’s wisdom, searching for solutions. The team found that the shelters could both be built with simple traditional building methods as the rainbow bridge with refined bamboo construction technologies. Finally, through craftsmen’s simple processing of raw bamboo, which Zhuguanlong township was richly endowed with, a woven bamboo structure with an 18-meter span was completed

The project built with locally obtained and recycled materials, which is people-centered, low-carbon and innovative. The design team thoroughly studied the possibility of recycling local materials. Field study showed that red soil on site was frequently used on local rammed-earth walls; bamboo woods prosper in mountainous lands along the site; dilapidated houses, which were being demolished at that time, could provide rubble from wall foundations and wood pieces from pillars and beams. As a result, recycled rubbles were used on newly built walls, while red soil on site was rammed into walls by local craftsmen; moso bamboo, through anti-corrosion treatment by the bamboo contractor, was assembled into large-span structures; recycled wood pieces was processed into wooden couches or wood bricks within rammed-earth walls. 

The design team also visited a stone processing factory to collect stone leftovers from processing, which were later cut into smaller pieces on both exterior and interior pavement. Those recycled materials, usually seen as wastes and thus coming at very low costs, were re-utilized by local villagers and craftsmen and extended their life in a new place, bearing our respect for people’s wisdom and labor. 

Zhuguanlong Tea Leaf Market is one project of the team’s series of sustainable practices and can be viewed as sustainable from environmental, social and economic perspectives. 
To achieve environmental sustainability, the project was built with locally obtained and recycled materials with low innate carbon footprint. Besides, it has made full use of natural ventilation, daylighting and rain-water landscapes, achieving harmony with surrounding natural lands. 

