    'Kindergarten Tocila, Prilep, N. Macedonia',
    'The Kindergarten in Tocila, Prilep, N.Macedonia, is a two story building, with a capacity for 252 children (aged 9 months to 6 years). The plot is 5030m2, of which 1530m2 is under the ground floor, and the rest is green open space (playground) and parking plots for bikes and cars (regulations). The design of the facility incorporates simple, yet powerful superposition of volumes, shapes and accented colors. The design is: innovative (following the principles of Neuro Architecture for children); inclusive (without architectural barriers in and outside the buildings); green and sustainable (passive solar design, energy efficiency, environmentally friendly, renewable energy sources), beneficial to the overall well-being of all occupants and economically viable The main idea was to design a projects that is green, sustainable, inclusive and adapted to the needs of every child. The building makes maximum use of the natural benefits offered by the sun. The location of the building within the boundaries of the site allows maximum use of the sun from the south side. All playrooms and nurseries (as well as the open-air playrooms) are with east, south-east, south and south-west direction, and have the possibility of natural ventilation and cooling throughout the year. The design of the facility incorporates simple, yet powerful superposition of volumes, shapes and accented colors (in the design of the floor plans, as well as in its spacial conception). All spaces are designed to benefit memory, improve cognitive capacity and improve mental stimulation of the children. The building has clear floor plans and clear visible circulation - central space and gallery halls that directly lead to each classroom on the ground and on the first floor. It provides landmarks for better orientation (colors and shapes), social spaces, enriched environments, natural light and open views to the green landscape surrounding the kindergarten.',
