    'Lakeshore Service Center',
    'The project is about a suburb area renovation in a mountainous college town in Zhuhai, Guangzhou, China. In the north of Fenghuang Mountain, the project is located on the Y104 country road, where two abandoned unfinished buildings had existed for decades. The surrounding environment was quite negative as well: A flood discharge channel on the northwest side of the site was blocked by weeds and silt, which posed a great safety hazard. The surrounding vegetation was lush, the trees were dominated by poinciana, forming a characteristic vegetation landscape.The project renovated the buildings as well as activated the whole site, and eventually succeeded in making the whole abandoned area into a dynamic public place. Challenge
After the COVID-19 pandemic, people are eager to venture outside and rebuild their public social relationships. During China''s rapid urbanization process, a large number of urban spaces were left without detailed design and planning, with some even located in important areas for communities and natural environments. By repurposing these areas, we can activate them and create vibrant community spaces. In the era of mobile internet represented by platforms like TikTok, these "small yet refined" urban living rooms will become important face-to-face socializing venues.
Contribution
The project is about a suburb area renovation in a mountainous college town in Zhuhai, Guangzhou, China. In the north of Fenghuang Mountain, the project is located on the Y104 country road, where two abandoned unfinished buildings had existed for decades. The surrounding environment was quite negative as well: A flood discharge channel on the northwest side of the site was blocked by weeds and silt, which posed a great safety hazard. The surrounding vegetation was lush, the trees were dominated by poinciana, forming a characteristic vegetation landscape. The project renovated the buildings as well as activated the whole site, and eventually succeeded in making the whole abandoned area into an activate public place.
The renovation work was carried out on the basis of respect for the existing elements. The structures of the two unfinished buildings were preserved. The building on the east side was originally designed to have four stories. After evaluating the view of the landscape along the lake side, we persuaded the owner to rebuild the building of two stories or lower, so that it could fit nicely along with the landscape of the valley with a humble gesture.
As for the landscape design, the features of the site have been largely retained. Specifically, vegetation and trees have been preserved to form landscape nodes. Meanwhile, safety risks were resolved. Taking into account that Zhuhai is often affected by typhoons in the summer, we dredged the originally blocked discharge channel in the process of lakeshore reconstruction. Also, a few landscapes walls were set aside inclined trees to prevent them from collapsing in the wind.
After the renovation, the landscape along the lake has once again opened. The revetment was reconstructed with gravel driveway, which often used by locals. All this has created a pleasant hydrophilic space. The outdoor area is particularly vibrant. Activities such as gatherings, photography, outdoor sports are taking place daily. Residents and college students spend their leisure time here meeting friends, chatting, and relaxing. In the study room lectures and salons are held occasionally. The roof platforms are used for rehearsals and BBQs. New memories and stories on the neighborhood are taking place.',
